From: chat-template-patches
Subject: [G9] Balance turn open/close for consecutive assistant messages

Targets: templates/gemma4/patched/{26B-A4B-it,31B-it,E2B-it,E4B-it}.jinja (state after G7 applied)

Failure mode. Two back-to-back assistant messages (no intervening user/tool)
render an ORPHANED `<turn|>` close with no matching `<|turn>` open. Upstream's
`continue_same_model_turn` rule (added intentionally) suppresses the SECOND
assistant's `<|turn>model` OPEN so the two share one turn — but the FIRST
assistant already emitted its `<turn|>` CLOSE at the end of its own loop
iteration. Net: one open, two closes for the merged turn. Reproduced on
`templates/gemma4/upstream/31B-it.jinja` with [user, assistant, assistant, user]:

    <|turn>user
    Hi<turn|>
    <|turn>model
    FIRST<turn|>          <-- premature close
    SECOND<turn|>         <-- orphaned close (no matching open)
    <|turn>user
    Next<turn|>

  → opens=3, closes=4. Breaks prefix/KV-cache symmetry and confuses parsers
  that pair turn markers.

Fix. Make the close mirror the open. The open is suppressed when the PREVIOUS
non-tool message is an assistant (`continue_same_model_turn`, backward scan).
G9 adds the symmetric FORWARD scan: when the NEXT non-tool message is an
assistant whose open will be suppressed, DEFER this message's close (emit a
newline so merged contents don't glue, but no `<turn|>`). The continuation
message emits the single close. Result for the case above:

    <|turn>model
    FIRST
    SECOND<turn|>         <-- one open, one close

  → balanced. Normal user/assistant alternation is byte-identical (the forward
  scan finds a non-assistant next message, so the close fires as before).

Scope. The defer is guarded with `and not ns_tr_out.flag` so G9 never touches
G7's tool-response close path. CONSEQUENCE: the rarer "assistant-with-
tool_responses immediately followed by a bare assistant" sequence retains the
pre-existing open/close asymmetry (the open-suppression fires but the close is
not deferred). That sequence was neither reported nor reproduced; fixing it
would entangle G9 with G7's tool-response handling. Left as a documented scope
boundary — see docs/PATCH-CATALOG.md § G9.

Sibling. Same close-marker logic as G7 (empty-content tool-call turn closure);
G9 is the consecutive-assistant case of turn-marker balance.

Stacks on G7. Diff is against the G7-applied state. The change is applied
identically to all four patched sizes; the hunk below for 26B-A4B-it is
representative.

--- a/templates/gemma4/patched/26B-A4B-it.jinja
+++ b/templates/gemma4/patched/26B-A4B-it.jinja
@@ -233,6 +233,15 @@
     {%- if not continue_same_model_turn -%}
         {{- '<|turn>' + role + '\n' }}
     {%- endif -%}
+    {#- G9: forward-scan to the next non-tool message. If it is an assistant whose <|turn>model open will be suppressed by continue_same_model_turn, defer THIS message's close so both share one balanced open/close pair (no orphaned <turn|>). -#}
+    {%- set next_nt = namespace(role=None, found=false) -%}
+    {%- for j in range(loop.index0 + 1, loop_messages | length) -%}
+        {%- if not next_nt.found and loop_messages[j]['role'] != 'tool' -%}
+            {%- set next_nt.role = loop_messages[j]['role'] -%}
+            {%- set next_nt.found = true -%}
+        {%- endif -%}
+    {%- endfor -%}
+    {%- set continued_by_model = (role == 'model' and next_nt.role == 'assistant') -%}

     {#- Render reasoning/reasoning_content as thinking channel -#}
     {%- set thinking_text = message.get('reasoning') or message.get('reasoning_content') -%}
@@ -338,6 +347,9 @@

         {%- if ns.prev_message_type == 'tool_call' and not ns_tr_out.flag -%}
             {{- '<|tool_response>' -}}
+        {%- elif continued_by_model and not ns_tr_out.flag -%}
+            {#- G9: defer close; the next assistant message continues this model turn (mirrors the open-suppression). Emit a newline so merged contents don't glue. -#}
+            {{- '\n' -}}
         {%- else -%}
             {{- '<turn|>\n' -}}
         {%- endif -%}
